  "text": "Firefox implements the Fetch API through WebIDL interface definitions in dom/webidl/ and their corresponding C++ bindings. The Request interface is defined in dom/webidl/Request.webidl and implemented in dom/fetch/Request.h and dom/fetch/Request.cpp. The Response interface is defined in dom/webidl/Response.webidl and implemented in dom/fetch/Response.h and dom/fetch/Response.cpp. The Headers interface is defined in dom/webidl/Headers.webidl and implemented in dom/fetch/Headers.h and dom/fetch/Headers.cpp. The FetchEvent interface is defined in dom/webidl/FetchEvent.webidl but its C++ implementation is located in dom/serviceworkers/ServiceWorkerEvents.h and dom/serviceworkers/ServiceWorkerEvents.cpp, as FetchEvent is a Service Worker specific event that extends ExtendableEvent. The FetchEvent class is implemented in ServiceWorkerEvents.h/cpp rather than in dom/fetch/ because it represents events dispatched in service worker contexts."
}

